section2/nosecrecy1: There were 3 polling stations in one classroom; voters generally had to leave their ID with the poll worker after they signed in and go to the judge to obtain their stamped ballot; the ballot box was placed directly in front of the poll worker table where they signed in, and it was situated on top if an identical empty ballot box. When one voter wanted to go to the secrecy station with just two stanchions for 3 stations the judge directed them to the ballot box to vote in front of the poll workers. section3/other:
This is a wafdeen station. The lines are long outside of the station and in a separate area outside there are long lines outside the center. The voters outside the Center reported waiting for up to five hours. Voters are pro and anti military. They are increasingly angry. One voter told us that voters are leaving because they cannot continue to wait.

The security officers were concerned about our safety observing in the station but us allowed it. The line outside cheered when they saw observers walk in. The judge has been extremely responsive and said he has asked for two more judges to add stations. They have not arrived yet.

The delay appears to be caused by the time it takes for polling officials go check voters' IDs against a registry via phone.

One wafdeen voter waited in line and was checked by the polling officials and told he could not vote.

section3/other:
At 8:35 we asked the judge at the station to observe the closing. He said yes but we had to leave first and come back just before nine. We returned at 8:50 and the security guards told us to wait outside. The judge then told us that our mandate was only to witness the voting, not the closing. He then left just before 9:00 and security did not let us view the closed station. The entire center closed early. There were no voters in line.

section3/prevented1: Upon entering PS, security extensively questioned our interpreter and made it difficult for us to observe the station. Again, because of our late arrival, we were not able to witness any voting and that is why this report is lacking detail.
section3/other: Security forces were filming most of the closing procedure , including the securing of the ballot boxes. The judge decided to put all of the center's ballot boxes in a separate room upstairs because it had a steel door and she considered it more secure. Security forces and the judge transported the ballot boxes to the other room and asked the center's second judge to place his boxes in the same room. The judge from our polling station then sealed the steel door with wax.
